abstract: Investors are cheered by reports from Ford, American Express and Microsoft that beat expectations.
snippet: Investors are cheered by reports from Ford, American Express and Microsoft that beat expectations.
lead_paragraph: Investors are unlikely to know the results of the government’s stress tests of major banks until May 4, but Wall Street cleared one hurdle on Friday: stocks did not lose their footing after regulators laid out how they were conducting the assessments.

headline.main: Wall St. Unfazed by Stress Test Details
headline.print_headline: Wall St. Unfazed by Stress Test Details

abstract: Chief executives and other corporate bosses are known for being big enthusiasts for the game of golf. It’s not unusual to hear about two C.E.O.s talking business on the greens — as the chiefs of Microsoft and Yahoo reportedly did last spring — or getting their latest golf scores posted on the Golf Handicap and Information Network.
